author: Gulli Arnason
title: National Airlines begins non-stop from Windsor International Airport to Orlando Sanford International Airport
text:
National Airlines begins non-stop from Windsor International Airport to Orlando Sanford International Airport 
  
National Airlines said it has begun non-stop service between Windsor, Ontario, (airport code YQG), and Orlando, Florida, (airport code SFB). 
The inaugural flight, on Thursday, December 17, 2015, will depart Windsor International Airport at 2:30 PM EST and arrive at Orlando Sanford International Airport at 5:00 PM EST. National Airlines will fly this route year ´round. 
After investigating numerous options, National Airlines chose Orlando Sanford International Airport because of its exceptional service, proximity to local attractions, and the relatively smaller crowds and shorter lines that will minimize time in the airport, leaving guests more time to enjoy all that Florida has to offer. 
National Airlines will also offer non-stop flights from Vancouver, British Columbia, (airport code YVR) and St. John´s, Newfoundland, (airport code YYT), to Orlando Sanford International Airport. Flights from these areas will take off mid-January 2016. Additionally, National will offer non-stops to Las Vegas, (airport code LAS), on December 27, 2015 and San Juan, Puerto Rico, (airport code SJU), on December 16, 2015. 
National Airlines is in the National Air Cargo Holdings family of enterprises. It provides sea-to-air multi-modal transportation and logistics solutions to get difficult-to-move cargo quickly and safely to wherever it must be moved. Established in 1990, the global reach of National Air Cargo Holdings is maintained via strategically located offices around the world centered at the US headquarters in Orlando, Florida, and with quality centers located in Germany, Japan, Malaysia, the Netherlands, Qatar and the United Arab Emirates.
